.SH "NAME"
rio_sport_is_active \- Tests if a switch port has an active connection\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ rio_sport_is_active('u
.BI "int rio_sport_is_active(struct\ rio_dev\ *\ " "rdev" ", int\ " "sp" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIrdev\fR
.RS 4
RapidIO device object
.RE
.PP
\fIsp\fR
.RS 4
Switch port number
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Reads the port error status CSR for a particular switch port to determine if the port has an active link\&. Returns
\fBRIO_PORT_N_ERR_STS_PORT_OK\fR
if the port is active or
\fB0\fR
if it is inactive\&.
